===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|sed}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|settle}}, {{m|enm|setle}}, {{m|enm|setel}}, {{m|enm|setil}}, {{m|enm|seotel}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|setl||that upon which one sits, a seat, a settle, a place to sit}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*setlaz||a seat; arm-chair}}, representing {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*sed-lo-}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*sed-||sit}}. Cognate with Dutch {{m|nl|zetel}}, German {{m|de|Sessel}}, Latin {{m|la|sella}}.

For the verb, compare Dutch {{m|nl|zetelen||to be established, settle}}.

